{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17645246","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17645246"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:14:49+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:14:49+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18100"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18100","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18100"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.1,0.05,0.8,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10814"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114317"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10814","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10814"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18100"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96317"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4934"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"10565"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25173"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25437"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114317","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/114317"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe prostate gland contributes approximately 30% of the total volume of seminal fluid. Its secretions are essential for normal reproductive function.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the composition of prostatic secretions?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Neutral fluid containing prostaglandins","Alkaline fluid containing sperm","Acidic fluid containing citrate","Alkaline fluid containing PSA and zinc","Acidic fluid containing fructose"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAlkaline fluid containing PSA and zinc\u003C/strong\u003E correctly describes prostatic secretions. The alkaline nature (pH 7.2-7.8) helps neutralise the acidic vaginal environment, while PSA helps liquefy the seminal coagulum after ejaculation. Zinc supports sperm membrane stability and has antimicrobial properties.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENeutral fluid containing prostaglandins\u003C/strong\u003E describes prostaglandins that are produced by seminal vesicles, not the prostate. \u003Cstrong\u003EAlkaline fluid containing sperm\u003C/strong\u003E refers to sperm that are produced in the testes, not the prostate. \u003Cstrong\u003EAcidic fluid containing citrate\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as while prostatic fluid does contain citrate, it is alkaline, not acidic. \u003Cstrong\u003EAcidic fluid containing fructose\u003C/strong\u003E describes seminal vesicle secretions, which provide energy for sperm.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Prostatic secretions are alkaline (pH 7.2-7.8) to neutralise acidic vaginal environment and enhance sperm survival.","The prostate produces prostate-specific antigen (PSA) which liquefies seminal coagulum.","Zinc in prostatic fluid supports sperm membrane stability and antimicrobial defence."],"references":["Hall JE. Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology. 14th ed. Philadelphia: Elsevier; 2021. Chapter 81; pg. 1014.","Tortora GJ, Derrickson BH, Burkett B, Peoples G, Dye D, Cooke J, et al. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, 2nd Asia-Pacific Edition. John Wiley \u0026 Sons, Limited; 2019."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96317"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18100"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96317","links":{"self":"https://ap